data.title: Arch of Hadrian, Athens, with the ruins of the Temples of Zeus Olympus in the background
meta_keywords: RIBApix - The UK's Largest Architecture Image Library - Architectural Images & Drawings
data.meta_description: NOTES: It is likely this drawing dates from between 1751 and 1754, during Stuart's extensive travels in Greece.This image also appeared as an engraving in Stuart & Revett's 'The Antiquities of Athens' (London, 1794), vol. III, ch. iii, pl. I.
